<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-08-14T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-08-14T10:00:00-05:00" n="600" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d600">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/1935: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-08-14T10:00:00-05:00">August 14, 1933—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 11:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>71. Legation’s 70, August 11, 1 p.m. Rio de Janeiro definitely agreed
                            upon and Brazilian Government informed. Peru suggests that negotiations
                            begin before October 1st if possible.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>